	(footprint "noknok:noknok_FlashPads_I2C-module_1x3_M2.5"
		(locked yes)
		(layer "F.Cu")
		(uuid "bcde76f9-4f7f-41cf-8d23-18402f7a37b0")
		(at 122.25 82.25)
		(descr "noknok flashing interface for CH32V003 I2C modules. Mounting hole at ORIGIN (0,0): M2.5, 2.5mm NPTH (Adafruit/Qwiic-aligned, nylon screw+standoff kit e.g. Adafruit 3299). 3 single-side SMD pogo pads (1=GND, 2=SWIO, 3=VCC) round Ø1.5mm on 2.54mm pitch, copper+mask only (NO paste); pad row offset +X and 1.25mm up (Y=-1.25), GND-to-hole = 3.75mm (~0.6mm pad-to-standoff clearance = metal-safe). SINGLE merged courtyard (hole keepout + pad strip as one F.CrtYd outline). The embedded hole sets the hole-to-pad spacing AND is the pogo-clamp orientation key. Authored on F.Cu - FLIP to bottom for bottom-side flashing. Shared-jig geometry: USB modules reuse the same hole-to-pad offset and add SWCLK at +2.54 from VCC. Standard placement: hole at 2.25mm/2.25mm from the board corner on all 20x20 I2C modules.")
		(tags "noknok flash pogo SWIO CH32V003 I2C programming testpad M2.5")
